snippet.textDisplay:
Nice trick:
Chill in fridge and some of the particulate solids settle. For a clearer stock carefully spoon-fill ice cube trays, leaving the layer of solids at the bottom of the container. Once frozen transfer to freezer zip bags. If you need a cup of stock, presto, 7 or eight cubes does the trick. No need to thaw the whole batch.
snippet.textOriginal:

snippet.textDisplay: I also have misophonia. I have tried my best to stop blaming myself and to reframe it as something that is not my fault. Even if they're not, at least now they know why you're always acting weird during meals.
